indimail (@version@-@release@) unstable; urgency=low

  * create_rpm: added --release option
  * indimail.spec: added explicit dependency of indimail-devel on libindimail version
  * renamed ChangeLog.indimail to ChangeLog
  * Shortened README-indimail after moving document to online wiki
  * Removed Provides: indimail-libs, libindimail from indimail package. Now available only in libindimail package
  * FreeBSD fixes fo vfstabNew.c, vadddomain.c, ProcessInFifo.c, pathToFilesystem.c, get_localtime.c, Makefile.am, configure.ac, default.configure
  * initsvc: enable and start services for FreeBSD
  * vsetpass.c, vchkpass.c, authpgsql.c, authindi.c print authmodule name in error logs/debug statements
  * pipe_exec.c: display authmodule being executed in debug statements
  * vsetpass.c, vchkpass.c, authpgsql.c, authindi.c, pipe_exec.c added pid error logs/debug statements
  * authindi: execute next module when already authenticated by previous module
  * authindi.c, check_quota.c, indisrvr.c, ismaildup.c, lockfile.c, monkey.c, osh.c, proxylogin.c, sslerator.c fixed compiler warnings
  * bulletin.c: initialize len variable
  * crc.c, configure.ac, inlookup.c, ProcessInFifo.c - Darwin Port
  * spam.c: initialize pos variable
  * vdeloldusers.c: initialize activecount variable
  * add_user_assign.c: BUG: wrong variable passed to do_assign2()
  * authindi.c: use AUTHADDR to determine if we are already authenticated
  * initsvc.c: changed Label for launchd unit file to org.indimail.svscan
  * Makefile.am: bypass linux specific code on Darwin
  * uninstall iauth.so, docs and post handle scripts
  * Makefile.am: Set LDPATH for libqmail path (Darwin)
  * initsvc: Fix for FreeBSD
  * fix for empty DISTRIB_ID on openSUSE, Suse causes indimail.[te][fc] to be missed out in the build.
  * ProcessInFifo.c: replace deprecated sys_siglist with strsignal
  * configure.ac: added check for strsignal function
  * recalc_quota.c: maildirquota problem: strnum2 variable wasn't getting set
  * configure.ac: set LDFLAGS -pie on Linux (primarily for openSUSE builds)
  * indimail.spec: fixed DISTRIB_ID and DISTRIB_VERSION for openSUSE, SLES builds
  * no_of_days.c: fixed no of days variabel getting clobbered due to use of stralloc_copyb() instead of stralloc_catb()
  * authindi.c: use _exit(2) as no buffers need to be flushed
  * get_assign.c, islocalif.c: added missing alloc_free
  * userinfo.c, vlimit.c: initialize struct tm for strptime() value too big error
  * vget_lastauth.c: null terminate ipaddr
  * GetSMTProute.c, vreorg.c: fixed infinite loop
  * skip_relay.c: new logic for terminating a line
  * postinstallation: update smtp authmodule with vchkpass                      
  * postinstallation: update imap/pop3, proxy imap/pop3 authmodule with authindi
  * indimail.h: added last_error_len field to dbinfo to keep track of allocated_length of last_error field
  * count_dir.c, dbload.c. get_assigh.c, inquery.c, islocalif.c, vdelfiles.c use alloc() instead of alloc_re()
  * LoadDbInfo.c: initialize last_error_len field of dbinfo
  * load_mysql.c: renamed closeLibrary() to incloseLibrary()
  * sql_getall.c: use allo_re() only for expansion
  * sq_vacation.c: drop supplementary privilges before setuid()
  * vbulletin.c, SendWelcomeMail.c, RemoteBulkMail.c, iadddomain.c, bulletin.c, bulk_mail.c use /var/indomain/domains for domain/bulk_mail
  * indimail.spec: fixed rplint error with unstripped binary or object
  * vdelivermail.c: skip creation of maildirfolder file for user's Maildir (INBOX)
  * indimail.spec: turn off lto
  * indimail.spec: turn on openSUSE permissions
  * removed sslerator
  * indimail.spec: stop/start svscan on upgrade
  * packaging: shutdown specific indimaail services instead of entire svscan service
  * handlers.c: use execv() instead of execute() in i_mount() function
